description: Held on the fourth Saturday of January each year, in Iloili City in the Philippines, the Dinagyang Festival is a religious and cultural celebration. In the late '70s, the traditional festival was rebranded and designed to attract tourism to the Philippines. Today, various regions throughout the country celebrate with warrior dances, massive parades and feasting. Innovations such as the carousel performance and mobile risers sprung from the Dinagyang Festival throughout the years.
